  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Transfer your<strong> BBQ pulled pork</strong> to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong>,<strong> </strong>draining away half<strong> </strong>of the juices</p><p>Add your <strong>ketchup</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and your <strong>ground cumin </strong>to the dish</p><p>Cover with <strong>tin foil </strong>and place the dish on a baking tray</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1647942014758-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1647942014758-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1647942014758-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1647942014758-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1647942014758-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>sweetcorn cobettes</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and seal the foil tightly around them</p><p>Add the <strong>foil-wrapped cobettes</strong> to a baking tray with the pulled pork and put the tray in the oven for an initial 20 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1647942020510-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1647942020510-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1647942020510-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1647942020510-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1647942020510-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries</p><p>Add the <strong>fries</strong> to a separate baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong>, the <strong>remaining ground smoked paprika</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>smoky fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1647942024536-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1647942024536-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1647942024536-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1647942024536-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1647942024536-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> chives</strong> finely</p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> with the <strong>chopped chives</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>cider vinegar</strong> (save the rest for later!) and a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>ranch dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1647942027912-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1647942027912-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1647942027912-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1647942027912-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1647942027912-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 20 min, remove the dish with the pulled pork from the oven and discard the <strong>tin foil</strong> covering the pulled pork</p><p>Pull the <strong>BBQ pulled pork</strong> apart using two forks (this technique is known as ‘pulling) and mix everything through the juices</p><p>Return the dish to the oven for 8-10 min further or until the sauce has been absorbed, the pork has started to crisp and the corn is tender – this is your <strong>BBQ</strong> <strong>pulled pork </strong>and <strong>roasted sweetcorn cobettes</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1647942033788-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1647942033788-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1647942033788-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1647942033788-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1647942033788-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>green</strong> <strong>chilli[es] </strong>in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a bowl with the <strong>remaining cider vinegar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>– this is your <strong>quick-pickled chilli</strong></p><p>Set aside for a couple of minutes, then drain the <strong>quick-pickled chilli</strong>, discard the liquid then return to the bowl and mix with your <strong>feta</strong> – this is your <strong>feta & quick-pickled chilli</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1647942036268-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1647942036268-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1647942036268-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1647942036268-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
